[ Applause ]

00:00:19.046 --> 00:00:20.546 A:middle
So welcome to "Ingredients
of Great Games".

00:00:21.066 --> 00:00:23.606 A:middle
What we're going to talk
about today is some things

00:00:23.636 --> 00:00:27.176 A:middle
that you can do in your game to
make it really, really great.

00:00:27.986 --> 00:00:30.876 A:middle
Because having a fun game
is simply not enough.

00:00:31.956 --> 00:00:34.236 A:middle
There are things
that great games do.

00:00:34.526 --> 00:00:37.826 A:middle
What I mean is, games that are
recognized as industry leading

00:00:38.376 --> 00:00:39.286 A:middle
in the games industry.

00:00:39.286 --> 00:00:40.926 A:middle
Things that they do
that you should be doing

00:00:41.056 --> 00:00:44.106 A:middle
or what you really need to be
doing to make your game great.

00:00:44.106 --> 00:00:46.726 A:middle
And there's a massive
opportunity.

00:00:47.396 --> 00:00:48.786 A:middle
As Tim talked about yesterday,

00:00:48.786 --> 00:00:53.276 A:middle
there's 75 billion
downloads of applications.

00:00:53.276 --> 00:00:55.446 A:middle
And as everyone in
this room knows,

00:00:55.446 --> 00:00:58.246 A:middle
a huge portion of
those are games.

00:00:59.886 --> 00:01:01.586 A:middle
Game Center also reinforces this


