00:01:01.586 --> 00:01:06.436 A:middle
with 130 million monthly
active users last month.

00:01:06.476 --> 00:01:10.456 A:middle
That is a huge audience that
you can tap into for your game.

00:01:11.516 --> 00:01:13.856 A:middle
But, and to do that, you need
to start with a great idea,

00:01:14.586 --> 00:01:18.826 A:middle
obviously put in hard work, and
you need to follow some really,

00:01:18.826 --> 00:01:21.976 A:middle
really important key tips
to make your game great.

00:01:23.486 --> 00:01:26.216 A:middle
So over the last couple days,
yesterday and this morning,

00:01:26.216 --> 00:01:27.766 A:middle
we've been talking
about technology.

00:01:28.846 --> 00:01:32.286 A:middle
And so technology like OpenGL
ES 3.0, which was introduced

00:01:32.286 --> 00:01:37.566 A:middle
since WWDC last year, and is
the most advanced OpenGL ES

00:01:37.566 --> 00:01:38.226 A:middle
out there.

00:01:38.706 --> 00:01:43.456 A:middle
We also have Metal, our low
level highly optimized GPU API.

00:01:44.216 --> 00:01:45.646 A:middle
We have Game Center,
which provides

00:01:45.876 --> 00:01:47.636 A:middle
that social connection
for your players.

00:01:48.546 --> 00:01:49.726 A:middle
SpriteKit and SceneKit.

00:01:50.606 --> 00:01:52.306 A:middle
You know, let us do the
heavy lifting for you.

00:01:52.656 --> 00:01:55.506 A:middle
If you don't need to go
right to OpenGL or Metal,

00:01:55.596 --> 00:01:56.956 A:middle
you can use SpriteKit
and SceneKit.

00:01:57.466 --> 00:02:00.876 A:middle
It'll allow you to do less
programming and let us build


