00:01:57.466 --> 00:02:00.876 A:middle
It'll allow you to do less
programming and let us build

00:02:00.876 --> 00:02:02.736 A:middle
out efficient API
underneath your game.

00:02:03.296 --> 00:02:06.956 A:middle
And Game Controllers: open your
game up to many forms of input.

00:02:08.166 --> 00:02:12.186 A:middle
Of course, there's also Xcode
6 with Swift and Playground.

00:02:12.666 --> 00:02:18.956 A:middle
We have tools like the
Metal or OpenGL Debuggers.

00:02:19.796 --> 00:02:22.246 A:middle
We have SceneKit and
SpriteKit editors.

00:02:23.206 --> 00:02:25.216 A:middle
And, also this week,
we have a mass amount

00:02:25.216 --> 00:02:26.906 A:middle
of sessions about games.

00:02:26.906 --> 00:02:31.736 A:middle
We have three on Metal, two
on SceneKit, two on SpriteKit.

00:02:31.736 --> 00:02:34.666 A:middle
We have labs on all of
these technologies all week,

00:02:34.666 --> 00:02:37.456 A:middle
and we have sessions
about developer tools.

00:02:38.296 --> 00:02:40.936 A:middle
But technology alone
is not enough.

00:02:41.406 --> 00:02:44.076 A:middle
You can't just take the
technology, build a game on top

00:02:44.076 --> 00:02:45.426 A:middle
of it, and expect
it to be successful.

00:02:45.886 --> 00:02:49.606 A:middle
You have to go about the games
business and the business

00:02:49.606 --> 00:02:52.386 A:middle
of building a game with the
same passion that you would go

00:02:52.386 --> 00:02:53.546 A:middle
about your game design

00:02:53.856 --> 00:02:56.576 A:middle
or choosing your technology
or your graphics API.

00:02:58.136 --> 00:02:59.926 A:middle
