00:04:28.746 --> 00:04:31.296 A:middle
And that's what I want to
talk to you about today.

00:04:31.886 --> 00:04:35.206 A:middle
So I'm going to go through a
list of some of these things

00:04:35.236 --> 00:04:36.756 A:middle
that just really
stand out to me.

00:04:36.756 --> 00:04:39.766 A:middle
There is a lot more than
what I'm going to go through,

00:04:39.766 --> 00:04:43.446 A:middle
but here is the first
thing on my list: Okay,

00:04:44.056 --> 00:04:45.706 A:middle
is to remove friction.

00:04:46.556 --> 00:04:50.256 A:middle
So I'm talking here about
making a great first impression

00:04:50.256 --> 00:04:53.916 A:middle
and a really frictionless first
time experience in the game,

00:04:54.366 --> 00:04:58.356 A:middle
really streamlining
everything that gets in the way

00:04:58.356 --> 00:05:01.066 A:middle
of the player getting into
the game as they start.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:04:58.356 --> 00:05:01.066 A:middle
of the player getting into
the game as they start.

00:05:01.356 --> 00:05:03.376 A:middle
So what do I really
mean by friction here?

00:05:04.176 --> 00:05:07.746 A:middle
So here's our imaginary
game, "Paddle Mania 3000".

00:05:07.746 --> 00:05:08.876 A:middle
It is awesome, by the way.

00:05:09.346 --> 00:05:12.506 A:middle
But it has some of the
problems with friction

00:05:12.506 --> 00:05:13.766 A:middle
that I'm thinking of here.

00:05:13.766 --> 00:05:16.206 A:middle
So let me show you first
the start up experience

00:05:16.206 --> 00:05:18.646 A:middle
of this game: Player comes in?

00:05:19.446 --> 00:05:22.576 A:middle
Loading. So, yeah,
still loading.

00:05:22.576 --> 00:05:24.776 A:middle
And it's going to take
it about a minute to load

00:05:24.776 --> 00:05:25.966 A:middle
because that's how
long it will take me

00:05:25.966 --> 00:05:27.046 A:middle
to get through the slide.

00:05:27.046 --> 00:05:30.766 A:middle
So, you know, the problem
that I have or that I see here

00:05:31.006 --> 00:05:33.806 A:middle
with a number of games is
that they really take kind

00:05:33.806 --> 00:05:37.466 A:middle
of a monolithic approach
to loading their assets.

00:05:37.906 --> 00:05:41.786 A:middle
And they preload everything
up front instead of, you know,

00:05:41.786 --> 00:05:44.626 A:middle
trying to just do what they
need just to get started.

00:05:45.536 --> 00:05:48.366 A:middle
So your goal should
be to get interactive

00:05:48.366 --> 00:05:49.926 A:middle
as quickly as you can.

00:05:50.216 --> 00:05:53.296 A:middle
Load just enough of your
assets so that you can get up

00:05:53.296 --> 00:05:55.616 A:middle
and running to your
first interactive screen.

00:05:55.616 --> 00:05:58.356 A:middle
And then use technologies
like Grand Central Dispatch,

00:05:58.356 --> 00:06:02.286 A:middle
and so on, to move work off
of your main thread and so,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:05:58.356 --> 00:06:02.286 A:middle
and so on, to move work off
of your main thread and so,

00:06:02.286 --> 00:06:04.326 A:middle
and let that continue
asynchronously.

00:06:05.136 --> 00:06:09.366 A:middle
Then, also, use the Time
Profiler to really take a look

00:06:09.366 --> 00:06:11.166 A:middle
at your loading performance.

00:06:11.616 --> 00:06:13.706 A:middle
And it will show you in a lot

00:06:13.706 --> 00:06:17.836 A:middle
of detail exactly what work the
app is doing during that time.

00:06:18.496 --> 00:06:21.396 A:middle
But even before you get into
the Time Profiler, I don't want

00:06:21.396 --> 00:06:24.376 A:middle
to just punt to the Time
Profiler as my advice.

00:06:24.756 --> 00:06:28.616 A:middle
You have to really think
about it first, right?

00:06:28.686 --> 00:06:31.546 A:middle
Why are so many things
being loaded up front?

00:06:32.036 --> 00:06:34.986 A:middle
And isn't there something
that could be deferred

00:06:34.986 --> 00:06:39.006 A:middle
and loaded asynchronously
a little bit later?

00:06:39.556 --> 00:06:41.726 A:middle
So, okay. So it's done loading.

00:06:41.726 --> 00:06:46.996 A:middle
And now let's go on to now
we're downloading some assets.

00:06:47.386 --> 00:06:50.896 A:middle
Okay. So, you know, a lot of
you guys do this in the game.

00:06:50.896 --> 00:06:51.596 A:middle
And it's fine.

00:06:51.626 --> 00:06:53.566 A:middle
In many cases, it's
a good thing.

00:06:54.026 --> 00:06:56.406 A:middle
But it doesn't have
to be something

00:06:56.406 --> 00:06:58.586 A:middle
where it makes the player wait.

00:06:59.306 --> 00:07:02.276 A:middle
So later in the talk I'm going
to go through a couple of things


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:06:59.306 --> 00:07:02.276 A:middle
So later in the talk I'm going
to go through a couple of things

00:07:02.276 --> 00:07:04.726 A:middle
that you can do to move
this off to the side

00:07:04.726 --> 00:07:07.056 A:middle
so the user doesn't
even have to notice it.

00:07:08.046 --> 00:07:11.256 A:middle
Okay, next: registration.

00:07:11.446 --> 00:07:13.366 A:middle
Would I like a "Paddle
Mania" account?

00:07:13.886 --> 00:07:16.386 A:middle
No, I would like to
play "Paddle Mania".

00:07:17.866 --> 00:07:21.156 A:middle
So, you know, when you think
about the registration,

00:07:21.496 --> 00:07:23.416 A:middle
there's a couple of
possibilities here.

00:07:23.896 --> 00:07:27.166 A:middle
You know, maybe, actually
that registration is needed.

00:07:27.166 --> 00:07:30.386 A:middle
Maybe you have a game
that is server backed,

00:07:30.896 --> 00:07:33.536 A:middle
and you need some way to
uniquely identify this player.

00:07:34.126 --> 00:07:35.486 A:middle
If that's the case,

00:07:35.486 --> 00:07:39.236 A:middle
then actually you could just use
the Vendor ID that we provide

00:07:39.306 --> 00:07:42.776 A:middle
to the game as the unique
identifier for that player.

00:07:42.776 --> 00:07:45.616 A:middle
And get it so that it's
out of the player's way.

00:07:45.916 --> 00:07:47.216 A:middle
Handle it automatically.

00:07:48.266 --> 00:07:51.426 A:middle
But maybe the case isn't that
you have a server backed game.

00:07:51.426 --> 00:07:53.906 A:middle
Maybe you're just asking the
user to sign up for an account

00:07:53.906 --> 00:07:57.526 A:middle
because you want to give
them news or special offers

00:07:57.526 --> 00:07:59.446 A:middle
or just whatever
the reason may be.


