Well, the first-time experience

00:08:02.516 --> 00:08:05.626 A:middle
in the game is not the right
time to ask for this yet.

00:08:05.926 --> 00:08:09.296 A:middle
They don't who, you know,
why you might be asking.

00:08:09.296 --> 00:08:12.226 A:middle
So, of course, you would
need to clearly explain it.

00:08:12.226 --> 00:08:13.226 A:middle
Like, is it needed?

00:08:13.226 --> 00:08:14.756 A:middle
Or is it just kind of extra?

00:08:14.756 --> 00:08:19.556 A:middle
And if it's not really needed,
then defer it until later.

00:08:20.016 --> 00:08:22.396 A:middle
So I want to play, I'm
going to say, no thanks.

00:08:24.066 --> 00:08:26.246 A:middle
Next, configure my paddle.

00:08:26.646 --> 00:08:27.596 A:middle
It's "Paddle Mania".

00:08:28.106 --> 00:08:30.236 A:middle
But, so, let me be clear:

00:08:30.566 --> 00:08:33.385 A:middle
If this is my first
time playing the game,

00:08:33.726 --> 00:08:35.606 A:middle
then I don't know the
implications of any

00:08:35.606 --> 00:08:38.056 A:middle
of these choices,
right, to go and play.

00:08:38.586 --> 00:08:42.256 A:middle
So if they matter, then
now is not the time

00:08:42.256 --> 00:08:43.775 A:middle
to ask me because I don't know.

00:08:44.496 --> 00:08:47.736 A:middle
And if they don't matter,
then don't put them in the way

00:08:47.736 --> 00:08:49.866 A:middle
of user getting onboard
into the game.

00:08:51.496 --> 00:08:55.476 A:middle
And, you know, not knowing
either way sort of conveys

00:08:55.476 --> 00:08:58.886 A:middle
to the players that it's not
really-the experience here

00:08:58.886 --> 00:09:00.446 A:middle
hadn't really been
thought through.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:08:58.886 --> 00:09:00.446 A:middle
hadn't really been
thought through.

00:09:00.656 --> 00:09:03.056 A:middle
And so there's some real trouble
with "Paddle Mania", actually.

00:09:04.156 --> 00:09:06.286 A:middle
And then, yeah, there we go.

00:09:06.856 --> 00:09:08.906 A:middle
The last one here:
please leave a rating.

00:09:08.906 --> 00:09:13.526 A:middle
You know, this is fine, right,
we talk about this all the time.

00:09:14.136 --> 00:09:17.356 A:middle
But, you know, at
this point, actually,

00:09:17.356 --> 00:09:19.106 A:middle
I haven't even played
the game yet.

00:09:19.106 --> 00:09:21.296 A:middle
So, you know, now is not
the best time to come

00:09:21.296 --> 00:09:22.756 A:middle
and ask me about rating it.

00:09:23.226 --> 00:09:26.086 A:middle
But, you know, I think, you
guys are getting it here, right.

00:09:26.156 --> 00:09:28.216 A:middle
So let me give you the
takeaways of this first section:

00:09:28.216 --> 00:09:30.686 A:middle
So you've got to get the
player into the game.

00:09:31.076 --> 00:09:34.236 A:middle
Reduce the load time
and any blocking updates

00:09:34.236 --> 00:09:37.306 A:middle
to get the game interactive
as quickly as possible.

00:09:37.776 --> 00:09:40.226 A:middle
Then streamline the
registration, right.

00:09:40.486 --> 00:09:43.866 A:middle
Provide an escape from
tutorials and long intros

00:09:43.866 --> 00:09:45.606 A:middle
and all those things that
might get in the way.

00:09:45.606 --> 00:09:49.846 A:middle
And then don't force
decisions about something

00:09:49.846 --> 00:09:52.846 A:middle
that the player can't
possibly know about yet.

00:09:53.316 --> 00:09:55.666 A:middle
And be patient, you
know, show some restraint

00:09:55.666 --> 00:09:57.296 A:middle
when you're asking for feedback.

00:09:58.626 --> 00:10:00.966 A:middle
So that's number
one: remove friction


