00:09:58.626 --> 00:10:00.966 A:middle
So that's number
one: remove friction

00:10:00.966 --> 00:10:02.766 A:middle
from the first time experience.

00:10:04.046 --> 00:10:07.146 A:middle
Okay, here's number
two: be a good teacher.

00:10:08.196 --> 00:10:11.766 A:middle
So being a good teacher is
really all about thinking

00:10:11.806 --> 00:10:13.496 A:middle
through that onboarding
experience

00:10:13.496 --> 00:10:15.316 A:middle
and really kind of
making it fun.

00:10:15.686 --> 00:10:19.826 A:middle
Because if you can help
your players get started,

00:10:19.826 --> 00:10:22.806 A:middle
it's more likely that they'll
become more deeply engaged

00:10:22.806 --> 00:10:23.676 A:middle
into the game.

00:10:24.126 --> 00:10:26.406 A:middle
And, you know, it's
almost easier to think

00:10:26.406 --> 00:10:27.576 A:middle
of it on the other side.

00:10:27.966 --> 00:10:30.806 A:middle
If you just leave it
to the player to figure

00:10:30.806 --> 00:10:34.596 A:middle
out your game themselves,
then you run a lot of risks.

00:10:34.596 --> 00:10:37.466 A:middle
You risk people just
failing a couple of times

00:10:37.466 --> 00:10:39.956 A:middle
and getting frustrated
and leaving the game.

00:10:40.396 --> 00:10:43.986 A:middle
Or maybe they'll miss something
that was really important

00:10:44.166 --> 00:10:46.696 A:middle
to the gameplay and would
have captured their interest,

00:10:46.926 --> 00:10:47.936 A:middle
but they just didn't see it.

00:10:47.936 --> 00:10:50.306 A:middle
They didn't know to
go down that path.

