performance issues with OpenGL,

00:37:26.866 --> 00:37:30.666 A:middle
it's usually because for some
portion of the frame, at least,

00:37:30.666 --> 00:37:33.646 A:middle
or maybe all of the frame,
they're trying to do a lot

00:37:33.646 --> 00:37:36.786 A:middle
of draw calls with a
low number of triangles

00:37:36.786 --> 00:37:38.806 A:middle
to be processed in
each draw call.

00:37:39.736 --> 00:37:45.116 A:middle
And the worst case scenario
is actually fairly common.

00:37:45.116 --> 00:37:46.096 A:middle
I see it sometimes.

00:37:46.096 --> 00:37:49.056 A:middle
It's particularly in
2D and isometric games

00:37:49.056 --> 00:37:50.356 A:middle
that I'll find this sometimes.

